A drive-by shooting in KZN's Sunnyside Park has left four males dead and one female injured. It's believed that occupants in a double cab bakkie were attacked by unknown suspects who fired shots at their vehicle. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A drive-by shooting in KwaZulu Natal's Sunnyside Park has left four males dead and one female injured. It's believed that at about 3:30pm on Tuesday, occupants in a double cab bakkie were attacked by unknown suspects who fired shots at their vehicle at Sunnyside T junction in Adams Mission. READ: Durban comedian shot in Wentworth The deceased are aged between 40 and 56-years-old while the 44-year-old woman has been transported to a local hospital.